19:13.970 --> 19:16.100
Is that a mutual decision?

19:17.400 --> 19:22.110
I mean,at first it was,but now I think it's more me.

19:22.210 --> 19:27.670
Well,with all the stuff that you have been through with the paternity and my affairs,

19:27.750 --> 19:30.340
it's no wonder that you're a little tentative.

19:30.500 --> 19:32.670
You make us seem so messed up.

19:32.760 --> 19:33.760
no,no.

19:33.820 --> 19:35.680
You're not messed up.

19:36.240 --> 19:38.540
I mean,look who you've chosen.

19:38.600 --> 19:43.630
I never had a boyfriend that was nice and kind and available.

19:43.730 --> 19:46.180
I mean,no one that I ever really liked.

19:46.900 --> 19:49.120
But,rebecca,you're not like me.

19:49.220 --> 19:50.860
Thank god.

19:53.790 --> 19:54.950
where did you go?

19:55.010 --> 19:56.370
the wax museum.

19:56.450 --> 19:59.480
When we passed in front of liberace,none of us said a word.

19:59.540 --> 20:00.630
Where are you now?

20:00.710 --> 20:03.480
You know that red double-decker bus that goes up and down hollywood boulevard?

20:03.570 --> 20:05.060
Oh,my god.

20:05.140 --> 20:06.420
You should see my parents.

20:06.500 --> 20:09.090
They're practically hanging off the side of the bus to get a good picture of

20:09.150 --> 20:11.660
the pirate in front of grauman's chinese theatre.

20:11.720 --> 20:13.320
You know what?They're having fun.You're bonding.

20:13.360 --> 20:15.290
Look,I gotta go.My destiny awaits.

20:15.370 --> 20:18.490
I can't wait to celebrate and get off this bus.

20:18.590 --> 20:20.110
Bye.

20:31.700 --> 20:34.030
kevin,it's good to see you.

20:34.150 --> 20:35.930
Listen,I want to give you a heads-up.

20:36.010 --> 20:39.180
I really think you deserve to be partner.

20:39.280 --> 20:40.760
It's been a long haul.

20:40.820 --> 20:43.780
It certainly has,but,uh,this makes it all worth it.

20:44.650 --> 20:46.070
Yeah,that's what I wanted to talk to you about.

20:46.150 --> 20:49.350
I,uh,I was outvoted at the partners' meeting.

20:50.200 --> 20:53.240
I did what I could.I honestly thought that you were a lock,but there was someone else

20:53.320 --> 20:55.580
that they were more interested in this year.

20:55.660 --> 20:59.070
Now it doesn't mean that you won't be considered in the future.

21:01.160 --> 21:02.450
Okay?

21:12.660 --> 21:14.180
Another bourbon on the rocks for you.

21:14.230 --> 21:20.070
No,but a driven bird coming at you is so much harder to get than one going away,like a quail.

21:20.130 --> 21:22.350
Well,I learned to shoot quail as a young boy,senator.

21:22.380 --> 21:23.790
Oh,well,then you know.

21:23.850 --> 21:27.690
There's just nothing better-- companionship,a good dog,a fine gun.

21:27.750 --> 21:30.910
Scotty used to pan fry them with gravy on the side,right?

21:31.010 --> 21:34.700
I don't remember the whole quail thing.

21:36.610 --> 21:38.570
Uh,do you cook,kitty?

21:38.780 --> 21:40.770
Uh,well,not quail.

21:41.050 --> 21:42.940
Well,and not like scotty.

21:44.640 --> 21:46.260
oh,look who's here.

21:48.330 --> 21:50.080
Here is your champagne.

21:50.110 --> 21:51.260
Thank you.

21:51.340 --> 21:53.390
So are you going to sit down,big shot,

21:53.480 --> 21:54.790
or are you too important fous now?

21:54.870 --> 21:56.020
Ohshut up.

21:56.100 --> 21:57.380
Did they give you the corner office?

21:57.440 --> 21:58.280
Not yet.

21:58.340 --> 22:00.480
Okay,well,here's a toast to my brother kevin.

22:01.090 --> 22:02.060
Congratulations.

22:02.140 --> 22:03.380
We're all really proud of you.

22:03.430 --> 22:04.240
Thank you.

22:04.320 --> 22:07.040
Here's hoping you're not involved in any of those frivolous lawsuits.

22:07.100 --> 22:10.150
I think you should listen to your brother-in-law on that particular topic.

22:12.050 --> 22:13.390
you all having a good time?

22:13.640 --> 22:16.200
Well,I was looking forward to sitting out on the patio.

22:18.020 --> 22:19.620
You know,I'm so sorry.

22:19.710 --> 22:20.840
The reservation got changed so many times-- you know what?

22:20.910 --> 22:23.630
I think this table is perfect.

22:23.740 --> 22:25.440
I-I think this is a good table.

22:25.530 --> 22:26.710
You do?

22:26.780 --> 22:28.680
It is a good table,I guess.

22:29.420 --> 22:31.190
Did you like the picture?

22:31.290 --> 22:34.750
Oh,yes.K-kitty,tell us more about the adoption.

22:34.810 --> 22:35.760
They loved it.

22:35.850 --> 22:37.600
I think that baby is going to be so lucky.

22:37.660 --> 22:39.960
I can't think of a better couple to raise a child.

22:40.030 --> 22:42.400
We--we actually think of ourselves as lucky.

22:42.580 --> 22:45.270
Well,we both admire you so much.

22:45.340 --> 22:47.070
We wanted to vote for you for president,but...

22:47.150 --> 22:50.330
scotty.I think I'm gonna have the lemon garlic prawns.

22:50.390 --> 22:51.980
Can I have a word with you?

22:54.970 --> 22:56.340
what?

23:00.400 --> 23:03.370
So I'm on the fourth hole at riviera--

23:03.450 --> 23:05.890
hogan's hole-- best par-3 in golf.

23:05.970 --> 23:07.310
I don't know it.

23:07.390 --> 23:08.390
Your husband did.

23:08.470 --> 23:10.230
He never made par there,though.

23:10.470 --> 23:14.880
You know,I enjoy an afternoon of golf as much as anyone,

23:14.960 --> 23:17.830
but I would really love it if we could get back to my proposal.

23:17.900 --> 23:18.680
Sorry.

23:18.760 --> 23:20.440
I get a little arried away when talking golf.

23:20.500 --> 23:23.290
You know,that's how I feel about this home.

23:23.350 --> 23:26.180
When--when people like us get sick,god forbid,

23:26.240 --> 23:30.790
we know that we can have our families around us because we have the resources to make that happen.

23:30.850 --> 23:32.880
But a lot of people who come here for medical care,

23:32.950 --> 23:37.140
they can't afford to put themselves up,especially when the cost of treatment is so exorbitant.

23:37.200 --> 23:41.120
Nora,this is a big enterprise you're proposing.

23:41.200 --> 23:45.330
And frankly,I'm a little nervous given your lack of experience.

23:45.410 --> 23:46.900
Yes.

23:47.470 --> 23:50.670
Yes,I know I have never run a business.

23:51.540 --> 23:54.290
But let me tell you,mr.Goldschmidt,

23:54.360 --> 23:56.650
I have run a household of seven.

23:56.710 --> 23:59.590
I know it's an unpaid and unappreciated position,

23:59.650 --> 24:04.540
but I defy you or any of your people I spoke with this morning to do

24:04.580 --> 24:07.700
what I did for the past 40 some odd years.

24:07.760 --> 24:12.680
I organized the schedules of five extremely well-rounded children.

24:12.740 --> 24:16.010
I ran carpools and bake sales and bluebird groups.

24:16.100 --> 24:19.430
I negotiated and mandated and coddled all at the same time,

24:19.490 --> 24:23.280
not to mention what I had to do for my husband to keep him happy and productive.

24:23.340 --> 24:26.300
And I did all of this without ever taking a sick day.

24:26.340 --> 24:30.340
The problem is no one values the experience of a stay-at-home parent,

24:30.410 --> 24:34.950
which is truly a shame,because basically,running this big enterprise,

24:35.030 --> 24:37.620
as you put it,would be a day at the beach for me.

24:38.130 --> 24:40.250
I'm sorry I got so carried away.

24:40.590 --> 24:42.260
Nora,wait.

24:43.230 --> 24:44.870
Come on.Sit down.

24:45.320 --> 24:46.930
Is this gonna be about golf?

24:47.010 --> 24:48.670
No,no golf.

24:48.740 --> 24:52.290
I'm not saying our working relationship is unmanageable,

24:52.330 --> 24:55.250
but--but how do I forget the way she came into the company?

24:55.310 --> 24:57.050
You know another thing is-- is rebecca.

24:57.110 --> 24:58.020
She's sweet.

24:58.080 --> 25:01.600
I love her like a sister-turned-not-sister and now my brother's girlfriend,

25:01.680 --> 25:07.910
and she does a great job,but it just-- it feels like their family business.

25:08.360 --> 25:10.000
I don't know,saul.

25:10.080 --> 25:11.170
About what?

25:11.230 --> 25:12.540
All of it.

25:13.230 --> 25:14.910
What are you,my shrink?

25:16.540 --> 25:18.070
I'm your uncle.

25:19.620 --> 25:25.400
I just want you to know that if there ever comes a time when you wantolly gone,I...

25:25.780 --> 25:27.460
you gonna rub her out?

25:27.560 --> 25:29.390
she's a co-owner.

25:29.470 --> 25:31.700
Sarah would come back in a second.

25:33.140 --> 25:34.590
What--what are you talking about?

25:34.640 --> 25:37.020
If getting rid of holly becomes a goal of yours,

25:37.080 --> 25:39.320
I want you to know that I would make it mine,too.

25:39.400 --> 25:40.820
That's all.

25:44.880 --> 25:47.230
told you that I would find the perfect moment,

25:47.300 --> 25:49.560
and guess what-- moment found.

25:52.780 --> 25:53.950
What,are you drunk?

25:54.010 --> 25:55.430
No,I'm not drunk.

25:55.740 --> 25:57.700
We were at a vineyard.I had a little wine.

25:57.760 --> 25:59.660
My mother was the designated driver.

25:59.720 --> 26:00.960
So she got you drunk?

26:01.040 --> 26:02.020
No,she didn't get me drunk.

26:02.100 --> 26:07.620
I suggested we open a bottle of wine after she totally confessed,unprompted.

26:07.980 --> 26:10.470
So what did she say?What is she gonna do?

26:10.550 --> 26:11.940
Nothing.

26:12.000 --> 26:13.400
She was just...

26:13.490 --> 26:18.020
confused and curious and wanted to feel in control.That's it.

26:18.080 --> 26:20.480
And you believe her?

26:21.280 --> 26:22.780
Justin,it was great.We talked for hours.

26:22.780 --> 26:26.130
I just--I don't see a reason for her to lie to me.

26:26.190 --> 26:28.220
It's never stopped her before.

26:29.700 --> 26:32.750
I'm sorry,but I think you're forgetting that the only reason

26:32.810 --> 26:36.190
why my mom actually knows about ryan is because your mother wanted to rub it in her face.

26:36.250 --> 26:38.410
Oh,like she wouldn't have found out anyway?

26:39.240 --> 26:40.510
Look,I'm--I'm--I'm sorry.

26:40.590 --> 26:42.540
I'm just having a tough time realizing how you go from "uh-oh,

26:42.620 --> 26:45.890
my psycho mom is on to something" to "uh,I believe everything she says.

26:45.970 --> 26:46.970
She's a changed woman.

26:47.040 --> 26:47.800
" You know what?Screw you.

26:47.800 --> 26:49.310
Why can't you just see her for what she is?

26:49.370 --> 26:50.440
What,do you have a blind spot?

26:50.510 --> 26:51.650
What are you saying,that I'm just like my mother?

26:51.720 --> 26:52.580
Because I'm not. -I never said that.

26:52.680 --> 26:54.610
Guess what.Your father--not exactly the perfect role model.

26:54.670 --> 26:55.910
What,are you comparing me to my father?

26:55.970 --> 26:57.120
Like what--why are you even with me then?

26:57.180 --> 26:58.690
-Because. -Why?

26:58.750 --> 26:59.670
You know what?Just get out.

26:59.740 --> 27:00.610
Rebecca-- get out.

27:00.670 --> 27:01.400
What do you think I'm gonna do,cheat on you?

27:01.400 --> 27:02.100
Is that it,you think I'm gonna cheat with you?

27:02.100 --> 27:04.060
Justin,I don't want to do this right now.This is my apartment.Leave.

27:04.120 --> 27:05.260
No,I asked you a question.

27:05.330 --> 27:06.210
Just get out!

27:06.290 --> 27:08.010
I'm not gonna leave you.

27:25.470 --> 27:29.540
I think it is wonderful you're having a baby at this point in your life.

27:29.620 --> 27:31.870
I had scotty at such a young age.

27:33.480 --> 27:35.320
Have you ever thought about adopting?

27:35.390 --> 27:38.250
Oh,maybe someday,but not right now.

27:38.310 --> 27:39.480
That's probably smart.

27:39.590 --> 27:40.530
no,no,no.

27:40.610 --> 27:43.910
I-I think that they would make amazing parents,even if they are democrats.

27:45.130 --> 27:49.160
speaking of which,can we tell you how much we enjoyed your tv show "red,white & blue"?

27:49.220 --> 27:51.820
So what was it like,interviewing all those famous types?

27:51.910 --> 27:53.320
That's actually how we met.

27:53.380 --> 27:55.400
oh,how romantic.

27:55.480 --> 27:59.230
Actually,we were told that we might meet some famous people ourselves,

27:59.290 --> 28:01.850
except I think they're all sitting out on the patio.

28:01.900 --> 28:03.980
You know what,bertha?I think that's enough.

28:05.520 --> 28:06.490
Excuse me?

28:06.570 --> 28:09.740
I'm sorry.I thought we came here to break the ice and to get to know each other,

28:09.780 --> 28:10.940
but I feel like I'm not even here.

28:11.010 --> 28:11.920
Kevin-- what?

28:12.000 --> 28:14.990
Can we please stop pretending that everything's fine and have a real conversation?

28:15.070 --> 28:16.340
I thought we were having one.

28:16.420 --> 28:19.290
No,no,that would require you to be a little less passive-aggressive.

28:19.350 --> 28:22.990
You can fawn over my sister and her husband because they're in your pantheon of republican gods,

28:23.070 --> 28:26.100
you can honor their version of the alternative family,but you know what?

28:26.160 --> 28:29.830
Maybe I'm not smart,but someday,maybe we would like to adopt.

28:29.910 --> 28:32.500
We drove here all the way from arizona.

28:32.560 --> 28:35.410
Okay,why don't we all just take a deep breath?

28:35.490 --> 28:36.900
I can breathe just fine.Thank you.

28:36.900 --> 28:39.450
You should hear him on a night when he doesn't make partner.

28:39.510 --> 28:42.900
Actually,I turned them down,'cause I'm so sick of being a lawyer.

28:42.960 --> 28:43.840
What do you-- what do you mean?

28:43.900 --> 28:44.720
Well,I have options.

28:44.790 --> 28:46.160
You see your two heroes here?

28:46.220 --> 28:48.120
They offered me a job.And guess what.Surprise,surprise.

28:48.180 --> 28:50.530
Your gay,democrat son-in-law is gonna take it.

28:50.770 --> 28:52.080
You're going to work for him?

28:52.140 --> 28:53.860
Try to be a little less enthusiastic.

28:53.920 --> 28:58.300
Yes,I am,because someone has to cross the aisle,or nothing gets done.

28:58.770 --> 29:00.290
I'm not hungry anymore.

29:00.350 --> 29:01.760
I want to go to the hotel.

29:01.840 --> 29:06.090
Mo-- I'm sorry.

29:06.150 --> 29:08.710
It was really a pleasure to meet you.

29:09.170 --> 29:11.290
What hotel did you put them up in?

29:11.850 --> 29:13.180
oh,my god.

29:13.280 --> 29:14.180
You forgot.

29:14.250 --> 29:15.400
I'm-- great.

29:15.460 --> 29:16.400
Scotty.

29:16.480 --> 29:17.880
Scotty.

29:22.580 --> 29:23.430
Hi,mom.

29:23.510 --> 29:25.230
Sarah,I didn't hold back.

29:25.310 --> 29:27.860
I-I practically lectured him,and guess what.

29:28.370 --> 29:31.070
Mr.Goldschmidt gave me a grant.

29:31.150 --> 29:33.460
Mom,that's fantastic!

29:33.910 --> 29:35.670
You were so right.

29:35.760 --> 29:37.840
I just needed a little confidence.

29:37.910 --> 29:39.150
You sound so happy.

29:39.220 --> 29:40.440
I'm almost jealous.

29:40.520 --> 29:41.450
Come to work for me.

29:41.530 --> 29:42.630
I'm serious.

29:42.710 --> 29:43.510
What's the pay?

29:43.570 --> 29:45.300
Nothing.It's a volunteer position.

29:45.360 --> 29:46.600
But maybe someday.

29:46.680 --> 29:48.180
Oh,sarah!

29:48.230 --> 29:51.370
It felt so good to be taken seriously.

29:51.440 --> 29:53.150
mama!Mama!

29:53.210 --> 29:54.380
Okay,mom,I gotta go.

29:54.440 --> 29:55.890
Congrats.

29:56.440 --> 29:58.620
cooper,what is it?

29:58.680 --> 30:01.490
Flashlight down,under the covers now.

30:01.570 --> 30:02.640
Look.

30:02.720 --> 30:04.100
Okay,I am gonna count to three.

30:04.190 --> 30:05.860
I want the flashlight on the bedside table.

30:05.920 --> 30:06.770
One...

30:06.850 --> 30:07.770
look!

30:07.840 --> 30:09.450
Two-- look!

30:10.350 --> 30:11.970
Oh,god.It's a caterpillar.

30:12.030 --> 30:14.310
Yeah,it turns into a butterfly.

30:14.400 --> 30:16.400
Okay,I'll take care of it.

30:16.480 --> 30:17.430
Can I hold it?

30:17.520 --> 30:18.380
No.

30:18.480 --> 30:19.940
Please.

30:21.110 --> 30:22.750
Will you go straight to sleep?

30:23.310 --> 30:24.140
Deal?

30:24.200 --> 30:25.430
Deal.

30:25.490 --> 30:26.700
Okay.

30:26.770 --> 30:29.740
Please get the flashlight out of my eyes.

30:34.160 --> 30:35.490
Put your hands out.

30:35.550 --> 30:37.820
Be very gentle.You don't want to squish him.

30:43.420 --> 30:47.010
Can we stay up until the butterfly comes?

30:47.250 --> 30:49.670
Well,that would be a very long time.

30:49.850 --> 30:51.320
Okay.

31:15.190 --> 31:17.610
so close to you did you find a hotel for your parents?

31:17.690 --> 31:19.170
Motel...

31:19.230 --> 31:20.800
in silver lake.

31:25.380 --> 31:26.780
scotty,I am so sorry.

31:26.840 --> 31:29.270
I asked for one weekend,kevin,one.

31:30.020 --> 31:32.500
Our entire lives are about your family.

31:32.560 --> 31:36.530
My parents visit us for the first time,and you can't show an ounce of restraint?

31:37.250 --> 31:38.790
I know.

31:38.850 --> 31:40.240
What is wrong with you?

31:40.320 --> 31:44.630
I mean,first you-- you introduce yourself by barging into their house on our wedding day,

31:44.710 --> 31:46.750
then you completely flip out at dinner.

31:46.810 --> 31:50.120
And after I put up with your endless work hours,your obsession over making partner,

31:50.180 --> 31:55.620
you blithely announce at dinner you're quitting your job to work for a republican.

31:56.490 --> 31:57.690
Maybe I could do some good.

31:57.770 --> 31:58.640
Have you lost your mind?

31:58.700 --> 32:00.570
I was just trying to get your parents to like me.

32:00.670 --> 32:01.880
Like you?I know.

32:01.940 --> 32:03.070
Now they hate me more than ever.

32:03.160 --> 32:04.880
Well,there's such a thing as cause and effect.

32:04.950 --> 32:05.920
I am so sorry.

32:06.000 --> 32:07.270
If I could take it back,of course I would.

32:07.330 --> 32:08.490
It was a bad day.

32:08.550 --> 32:09.850
Yeah,you can say that again.

32:09.930 --> 32:11.630
I didn't make partner.

32:12.220 --> 32:14.030
They gave it to someone else.

32:14.130 --> 32:17.600
And I couldn't say anything at dinner because I was so humiliated.

32:18.240 --> 32:21.880
This is by no means an excuse,but when I left work,

32:22.000 --> 32:24.940
all I could think of was getting to you because I knew once I'd see you,

32:25.020 --> 32:27.030
I would feel okay,and when I got there,

32:27.090 --> 32:33.420
the only pair of eyes that I wanted to see were yours because all I wanted was a hug.

32:33.990 --> 32:37.640
I don't blame you at all,because we agreed,no P.D.A.

32:39.890 --> 32:44.390
-Come here. -I swear I will make it up to them.

32:56.240 --> 32:57.900
I mean,wow.

32:58.040 --> 33:00.250
I can't believe we waited that long.

33:00.410 --> 33:01.420
We're idiots.

33:01.480 --> 33:02.900
What were we thinking?

33:02.950 --> 33:03.980
We were thinking too much.

33:04.040 --> 33:05.650
That's what we were thinking.

33:05.770 --> 33:07.210
I'm done thinking.

33:07.290 --> 33:08.820
Me,too.

33:09.960 --> 33:13.040
I can't believe we had fight sex before we had real sex.

33:13.140 --> 33:15.220
I think it counts as real sex.

33:16.280 --> 33:19.230
Besides,I have no idea what we were actually fighting about.

33:19.680 --> 33:21.550
That's because it wasn't our fight.

33:22.730 --> 33:24.810
Although you do pack a punch.

33:26.820 --> 33:29.320
I think I know what we need to do.

33:33.730 --> 33:35.090
I have an idea.

33:35.990 --> 33:37.000
Not that.

33:37.080 --> 33:38.400
Not that I don't want to do that,too.

33:38.490 --> 33:40.520
I'm just--I'm talking about our moms.

33:40.830 --> 33:42.290
Well,that's a buzzkill.

33:43.280 --> 33:45.940
I think you should listen to my idea first.

33:52.690 --> 33:55.800
,I,uh,I made some sandwiches for the road.

33:55.840 --> 33:57.200
Oh,there's some banana bread in there,too.

33:57.260 --> 33:58.430
Sounds delicious,honey.

33:58.490 --> 33:59.720
Uh,do you need directions?

33:59.800 --> 34:02.650
No,we've got the gps in the car,but,uh,thanks anyway.

34:04.390 --> 34:05.850
Look,um,I'D...

34:05.930 --> 34:08.170
I'd like to apologize again for the other night.

34:08.230 --> 34:09.989
It was-- water under the bridge.

34:10.050 --> 34:11.679
We're sorry you didn't make partner.

34:11.719 --> 34:13.190
Thank you.

34:13.560 --> 34:15.550
This is for you.

34:15.949 --> 34:19.469
It's a bottle of bourbon,whicis what I should've got you in the first place.

34:19.500 --> 34:21.900
You're determined to get me drunk,aren't you?

34:21.960 --> 34:24.219
Well,I appreciate this,but I'll tell you what--

34:24.460 --> 34:27.969
why don't I take the scotch back with me,you take this,

34:28.050 --> 34:31.139
and in a few months,maybe we'll,uh,compare notes?

34:32.120 --> 34:33.750
I'd be very glad to.

34:34.040 --> 34:37.179
Someone's gonna have to cross the aisle,or nothing's gonna get done.

34:40.710 --> 34:42.449
well,we-- we better get going.

34:53.230 --> 34:55.250
I'm gonna let you go down that list.

34:55.600 --> 34:57.660
Offer the position to one of your other clients.

34:57.720 --> 34:58.880
I'm a little surprised.

34:58.960 --> 35:00.380
Kids stop driving you crazy?

35:00.750 --> 35:02.550
No,never.

35:02.710 --> 35:04.140
But,you know...

35:05.090 --> 35:06.490
no.

35:06.770 --> 35:10.320
Look,it's a decent position,and god knows,I'm gonna need a job.

35:10.330 --> 35:13.590
But right now,hanging out with my kids is pretty cool,

35:13.670 --> 35:18.220
and if I'm gonna give that up,it can't be for something that's just decent.

35:18.280 --> 35:19.900
Find me something...

35:19.980 --> 35:22.600
better,something great.

35:22.680 --> 35:24.980
And,uh,then we'll talk.

35:34.920 --> 35:36.690
what,you don't lock the door anymore?

35:36.750 --> 35:38.240
What happened to the secret service?

35:38.320 --> 35:40.040
I'm not running for president anymore.

35:40.120 --> 35:41.900
Nobodyares if you shoot me.

35:42.420 --> 35:43.970
Hello to you,toO.

35:44.030 --> 35:46.410
Honey,did you,um,happen to make another...

35:46.510 --> 35:48.420
oh,we have company.

35:48.520 --> 35:50.010
Hey.

35:50.540 --> 35:52.070
How are you doing?

35:52.150 --> 35:53.440
Fine,believe it or not.

35:53.520 --> 35:57.440
Um,but I do want to apologize for the other night.

35:57.520 --> 35:58.430
Oh,no,no,don'T.

35:58.520 --> 36:00.220
You know,it was actually nice that--

36:00.300 --> 36:04.000
that you thought that maybe we would have a little power over them.

36:04.080 --> 36:07.290
You never made partner,did you?

36:08.380 --> 36:10.370
No.No,I didn'T.

36:10.450 --> 36:13.330
And it was kinda hard to admit at the time.

36:14.490 --> 36:16.200
I'm sorry,kev.

36:16.300 --> 36:19.430
Hey,I'll give a reference to whoever you'd like.

36:19.710 --> 36:21.810
I think you'd make a great barista.

36:22.420 --> 36:24.340
actually,I want to work for you.

36:25.420 --> 36:28.210
You're being serious now,so I--I'm not getting it.

36:28.280 --> 36:30.430
I've spent a long time demonizing you.

36:30.510 --> 36:31.530
Still not getting it.

36:31.610 --> 36:33.760
Okay,when I first met scotty's parents,

36:33.810 --> 36:36.140
I realized that demonizing someone can cut both ways.

36:36.200 --> 36:38.510
Now I'm not saying I can change that.

36:38.570 --> 36:40.320
But I do have a knack for stirring things up.

36:40.400 --> 36:43.720
right.Which I-I don't think is such a great qualification.

36:43.780 --> 36:46.890
I don't think you think that,otherwise you wouldn't have offered me the job.

36:46.950 --> 36:50.050
I think you have to admit,the other night was kind of amazing.

36:50.120 --> 36:52.630
Cause to tell the truth,scotty's parents and i are

36:52.690 --> 36:55.650
 in a much better place now than if we'd talked about elk for three hours.

36:55.710 --> 36:57.660
Quail,but go ahead.

36:57.720 --> 37:01.170
Okay,all I'm asking is that you hear me out,

37:01.230 --> 37:03.890
and if we meet in the middle,that's good enough for me.

37:04.690 --> 37:09.110
Well,I would love to hear you out,but when you didn't respond initially,

37:09.210 --> 37:14.090
we got other candidates,uh,most of whom are very,you know,qualified.

37:14.150 --> 37:16.750
Yeah,with far less emotional baggage.

37:17.060 --> 37:18.120
Okay,I get it.

37:18.200 --> 37:19.790
Let me have it.I deserve it.

37:19.830 --> 37:22.390
We'd love to,but we're extremely busy.

37:24.320 --> 37:26.140
Senate bill 237.

37:26.180 --> 37:27.520
Read it.

37:27.580 --> 37:29.140
Give me an opinion.

37:30.540 --> 37:32.140
Glad to have you.

37:35.710 --> 37:37.270
Talk about hitting the ground running.

37:37.330 --> 37:39.190
Welcome to politics.

37:42.450 --> 37:44.060
God,justin,look who's here.

37:44.120 --> 37:45.500
I know.Come on.

37:45.560 --> 37:46.970
What's going on?

37:50.770 --> 37:52.320
Hello,nora.

37:52.420 --> 37:54.050
What a surprise.

37:54.870 --> 37:58.260
All right,look,we decided that you guys need to deal with this whole ryan situation yourselves.

37:58.320 --> 37:59.810
What are you talking about?

37:59.930 --> 38:01.530
Uh,sorry,mom,but I-I found this,

38:01.610 --> 38:03.950
and I know I probably should've told you earlier.

38:04.010 --> 38:08.430
Mom,this is,uh,information on ryan lafferty that rebecca found on holly's desk.

38:09.350 --> 38:10.840
-At is this? -Rebecca.

38:10.900 --> 38:12.410
I'm sorry,but you guys need to deal with this.

38:12.470 --> 38:14.860
If rebecca and i are gonna have any chance,this can't be our problem.

38:14.920 --> 38:16.670
I'm sure you guys will figure it out,so...

38:16.720 --> 38:18.530
so on that note,mom,have a seat.

38:18.630 --> 38:19.680
Good luck.

38:19.760 --> 38:22.030
And,uh,try the,uh,the seafoosalad.

38:22.120 --> 38:23.790
It's fantastic.

38:33.980 --> 38:35.780
Did you contact ryan?

38:35.880 --> 38:37.180
No.

38:37.500 --> 38:41.030
But,oh,I was tempted to.

38:41.910 --> 38:43.700
Oh,holly.

38:43.760 --> 38:46.890
I know more than anyone what you're going through.

38:47.410 --> 38:49.960
I suggest you let william go.

38:50.060 --> 38:55.460
My only interest in ryan has nothing to do with his father.

38:55.850 --> 38:59.620
Why is it I think the only thing left for you to be interested in 

38:59.680 --> 39:04.060
would be making my life asncomfortable as possle?

39:04.740 --> 39:08.010
how typically narcissistic of you.

39:08.070 --> 39:10.210
I like to think of it as self-preservation.

39:10.290 --> 39:13.460
Holly,I'm telling you,this is better left alone.

39:13.540 --> 39:17.260
Mm,right,the way sarah left it alone when she told rebecca

39:17.340 --> 39:21.590
that william was her father after I begged her not to,which by the way,

39:21.670 --> 39:23.590
turned out not even to be true.

39:23.650 --> 39:25.810
And we have barely recovered from all of that.

39:25.870 --> 39:27.850
Why would you even consider doing this?

39:27.940 --> 39:29.860
Well,it might be fun.

39:32.150 --> 39:37.250
You know,it--it is so amusing watching you panic

39:37.310 --> 39:40.310
when things don't turn out exactly the way you have it planned,

39:40.390 --> 39:46.700
and,oh,god forbid that I upset your perfect little apple cart.

39:46.780 --> 39:50.540
Well,at least I have an apple cart.

39:50.640 --> 39:55.800
you know,holly,I-I really think it's your jealousy that makes me pity you the most.

39:55.960 --> 39:57.560
Pity?

39:57.620 --> 40:02.910
And I don't believe for one minute you'd be willing to jeopardize your relationship with rebecca,

40:02.950 --> 40:08.030
because if you do anything-- I never said that I was going to do anything.

40:08.090 --> 40:10.300
I probably won'T.

40:11.930 --> 40:16.770
But then again,I do have these bad days...

40:19.460 --> 40:22.540
maybe you should call him.

40:22.790 --> 40:25.100
It's probably best...

40:25.180 --> 40:27.600
if you found him first.

40:30.150 --> 40:32.190
Have a nice day,nora.

